{"questionId":"31430872","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Srinivasa places the nine labelled balls shown below into a box.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/8553f4d517537fd22535c2bf9531ddaae86ee4bc.png\"></p>\n<p>Srinivasa then chooses two balls at random, one at a time, from the box. The first ball is <strong>not&nbsp;replaced</strong> before he chooses the second.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that both balls chosen are labelled <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>N</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note: </strong>Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for a correct compound probability calculation seen.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>72</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>36</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0278</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0277777</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>78</mn><mo>%</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)&nbsp; (C2)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"31430872","referenceCode":"20N.1.SL.TZ0.T_6c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the probability that both balls chosen are labelled N.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence,